<p>Afghanistan&#x27;s Taliban government and Pakistan agreed Sunday to an immediate ceasefire after a week of cross-border clashes, following talks in Doha mediated by Qatar and Turkey [bbc.com#1][abcnews.go.com#2][france24.com#1][pbs.org#1]. Qatar said the truce takes effect right away and that follow-up talks are planned to work toward a lasting framework [euronews.com#1]. The flare-up was described as the worst violence between the neighbors since 2021, and observers caution that fundamental disputes remain unresolved [france24.com#1][nytimes.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/j5dz3E4XqiLi9Zqla20aA2NOaWPxS6eWXq7SkznFzCXy0Jq21nG_I-PvunWizwLdzFAPLDNsggnGFIf2HwcA1QhmiZCm0gfmRHpXWG0ZzttX' alt='Defence ministers of Pakistan and Afghanistan sign the ceasefire agreement in Doha on October 19.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Next meeting: Pakistan said delegations will reconvene in Istanbul on October 25 to discuss a concrete, verifiable monitoring mechanism [dawn.com#1][dawn.com#2].</li><li>Venue variance: Qatar’s foreign ministry separately indicated subsequent talks would continue in Qatar, highlighting evolving logistics while the truce holds [euronews.com#1].</li><li>Security concerns: Pakistan linked the crisis to attacks it says originate from Afghan soil and said it recently struck Gul Bahadur group camps inside Afghanistan before the truce [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Sovereignty pledge: Both sides pledged to respect each other’s territory and sovereignty as part of the Doha understanding [dawn.com#1][dawn.com#2].</li><li>Casualty claims: Each side claimed heavy casualties during the flare-up, underscoring lingering mistrust despite the ceasefire [bbc.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>A ceasefire agreement has been finalised. The terrorist attacks from Afghanistan on Pakistan’s soil will cease immediately. Both neighbouring countries will respect each other’s territory. - Khawaja Asif</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Government of Pakistan: Deputy PM and Foreign Minister Ishaq Dar called the deal &#x27;the first step in the right direction&#x27; and pushed for a &#x27;concrete and verifiable monitoring mechanism&#x27; at the next meeting. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949921/first-step-in-right-direction-political-figures-other-nations-welcome-pakistan-afghanistan-ceasefire-pact'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Afghan authorities: Afghanistan denies harbouring militants who carry out attacks in border areas. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/south-asia/article/3329583/afghanistan-and-pakistan-agree-ceasefire-after-deadly-fighting'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Regional analysts: Experts warned the ceasefire is fragile and core disputes remain unresolved. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/19/world/asia/afghanistan-pakistan-cease-fire.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/afghanistan-and-pakistan-agree-to-respect-ceasefire-mediated-by-qatar-and-turkey'>Afghanistan and Pakistan agree to respect ceasefire mediated by Qatar and Turkey</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/19/afghanistan-and-pakistan-agree-to-immediate-ceasefire-qatars-foreign-ministry-says'>Afghanistan and Pakistan agree to immediate ceasefire, Qatar&#x27;s Foreign Ministry says</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949845/pakistan-afghanistan-agree-to-immediate-ceasefire-after-doha-talks-defence-minister'>Pakistan, Afghanistan agree to immediate ceasefire after Doha talks: defence minister</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cze6nzpl74do'>Taliban and Pakistan agree to ceasefire after days of deadly clashes</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/south-asia/article/3329583/afghanistan-and-pakistan-agree-ceasefire-after-deadly-fighting'>Pakistan and Afghanistan agree to ceasefire after deadly fighting</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/inter